Package: bestfitr
Title: Bayesian Flood-Frequency and Extreme-Value Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Cam", "Bracken", email = "cameron.bracken@pm.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: R bindings to a shared C++ port of the USACE-RMC Numerics and
    RMC.BestFit libraries for flood-frequency and extreme-value analysis. This
    early version exposes the Generalized Extreme Value distribution: density,
    distribution and quantile functions, moments, parameter estimation
    (method of moments, L-moments, maximum likelihood), and quantile uncertainty.
License: file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
LinkingTo: cpp11
SystemRequirements: C++17
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    jsonlite
Config/testthat/edition: 3
URL: https://cameronbracken.github.io/bestfit/r/, https://github.com/cameronbracken/bestfit
BugReports: https://github.com/cameronbracken/bestfit/issues
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
